# Git LFS routing for large bundled binaries.
#
# This file is picked up automatically when the repo is under Git with
# Git LFS installed (`git lfs install` once per clone). Files matching
# below are stored as LFS pointers, not as raw blobs, so a push doesn't
# try to upload ~800 MB through GitHub's per-file blob path (100 MB
# hard cap) and so day-to-day clones stay fast.
#
# Currently bundled:
#   worker/data/mp_xrd_database.db — 784 MB Materials Project XRD DB
#   (154,879 phases). See worker/README.md "Materials Project XRD
#   database" for the refresh / regen source in lattice-cli.
#
# To activate LFS when first cloning:
#   1. Install git-lfs (https://git-lfs.com/) if not already.
#   2. `git lfs install` in this repo (writes hooks).
#   3. Normal `git clone` thereafter fetches the pointer + the binary.
#
# If you're re-rolling the DB (refreshed MP export, version bump):
#   - just replace `worker/data/mp_xrd_database.db` with the new file.
#   - `git add worker/data/mp_xrd_database.db` — LFS picks it up via
#     this .gitattributes entry; no extra `git lfs track` command
#     needed since the pattern is already committed here.

worker/data/*.db filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
